questions.scenario:
You are debugging a production issue where a transaction-heavy Spring Boot service is experiencing silent data inconsistency. The developer wrote the following class to update a user's balance and log the transaction asynchronously:

java
@Service
public class UserService {
    @Autowired private TransactionTemplate transactionTemplate;

    @Transactional
    public void updateBalanceAndLog(Long userId, BigDecimal amount) {
        updateBalance(userId, amount);
        CompletableFuture.runAsync(() -> logTransaction(userId, amount));
    }

    private void updateBalance(Long userId, BigDecimal amount) {
        // Database update logic
    }

    @Transactional(propagation = Propagation.REQUIRES_NEW)
    public void logTransaction(Long userId, BigDecimal amount) {
        // Insert transaction log
    }
}


The log table is missing records, and no exceptions are logged, even though `updateBalance` completes successfully.
